  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A vial of lightly filtered Laublub oil. Safe for Delta Kilo Autarchs to consume as lubricant.</p><h2>Drink</h2><p>Target a creature and choose how many charges to feed it (Consumption Scaling). Each charge consumed restores 1 hour to the target's fluid gauge, up to the 48-hour cap. Only meaningful if the target is a Delta Kilo Autarch; excess beyond the cap is wasted.</p><h2>Douse</h2><p>Pour charges onto the ground to coat the area with oil (radius scales with charges spent: 1 charge = 2.5 ft radius, 2 = 3.75 ft, 3 = 5 ft). Any creature entering or starting its turn there must succeed on a DC 10 + the douser's Dexterity modifier Dexterity saving throw or fall prone (and take 1d6 fire damage if the oil has been ignited; standing up requires the same save). The oil evaporates after 1 minute. Igniting is GM adjudicated and grants a one-time +2 bonus to the triggering fire damage.</p><h2>Throw</h2><p>Ranged attack roll against a creature or object. On a hit, the target is coated in oil for 12 rounds. At the start of its turn, the target may spend its action and succeed on a DC 10 Dexterity saving throw to reduce the remaining duration by 5 rounds. Igniting (GM adjudicated) grants a one-time +2 bonus to the triggering fire damage.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
